pros:
1. A relatively good benefits package;
2. An organisation that really looks after its staff;
3. High level of support offered to staff during the COVID pandemic;
4. Passionate about environmental & social governance;
5. Lots of opportunities for learning & development.

cons:
1. Career development is very much dependent on the support received from your management team (regardless of your personal work efforts/achievements);
2. A lack of transparency exists across regions for team members performing a similar role, although treated differently (in the way of job titles and bands).
3. Salary is middle-of-the-range as to competitiveness within the financial services market.
